Chelsea has finally decided to sell Nigerian striker, Ike Ugbo, this summer’s transfer window, according to football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano. Romano made this known in a tweet via his Twitter account on Wednesday. Ugbo is currently on loan at Cercle Brugge from Chelsea. His contract at Chelsea is set to expire in June 2022. The 22-year-old has already opened contract talks with Monaco, Fulham and Eintracht Frankfurt. Ugbo scored 16 goals for Cercle Brugge this season. “Chelsea is prepared to sell Ike Ugbo on a permanent deal this summer with many clubs interested in the striker,” Romano tweeted. “He has decided to leave Cercle Brugge after scoring 16 goals this season on loan. Monaco, Fulham and Eintracht Frankfurt have opened talks to sign Ugbo.”